body": "Having a `.git` file pointing to the location of the git-dir is a legit dataset setup. However, the `ConfigManager` insists on monitoring `<dsroot>/.git/config`. A file which may not exist.\r\n\r\nIn such a case the decision making of when to reload the configuration is impaired, as mtime assessment will be incomplete.\r\n\r\nMoreover, the location of the `local` config file is configured once at the creation of the config manager, hence will never change for a repository/dataset instance, because we use singletons.\r\n\r\nThis is not an issue for configuration modification, because we call `git-config` which does the right thing. But any `ConfigManager.reload(force=False)` will not pick up changes to the local configuration.\r\n\r\nDiscovered looking at the error in #4808 (which uses a file placed next to `ConfigManager._repo_cfgfname`, which points to the wrong location for any submodule that has not yet been processed by `_fixup_submodule_dotgit_setup()`.", "closed_by": {"login": "mih", "id": 136479, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEzNjQ3OQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/136479?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih", "html_url": "https://github.com/mih", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/4809/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 